My pickup order I ordered online was on-time and I'm sure the staff here are lovely, but my chicken Caesar salad was vastly underwhelming. Thankfully the romaine and bread were of decent quality and tasty, but the other components were mediocre in flavor and texture. "Grilled" chicken chunks were small, soft/mushy and plain. Strips of Parmesan were waxy and bland. Croutons were small and had unappealing consistency like they weren't made from actual bread. Most terrible was the kale pesto dressing which had no substance, was completely flavorless and made the salad greasy in a way that a dressing made of olive oil wouldn't have.. I might order from here again in a pinch, but this salad struck me as low quality. Can't begin to compare to a salad from similar restaurants such as Chopt, Sweetgreen (my personal favorite), or even Lenwich. Maybe I'm asking too much for this price point in this neighborhood; perhaps a more complex and expensive salad from the menu would have been enjoyable.

So today after a tiring indoor soccer game I was excited to see that a Just Salad was open right around the corner. I WAS a loyal customer and have spent a huge amount of money at other just salad locations. However, this was my first time at this specific location and my LAST time in any Just Salad. It was very clear to me that I, the customer, was not important to the staff. When entering the store I greeted the staff and asked where the proper station to place my order was. The person behind the bar ( the one who made the salads told me to go to the side). Then, after standing there for 5 minutes waiting to place my order, the person who I believe is the manager said to me with an attitude "oh he didn't tell you we're closed" then proceeded to lash out at the worker who had begun to put on gloves because I believe he was about to take my order. She told him "why didn't you tell him we were closed". Disgusted, I left the establishment. I will NO LONGER be a proud customer of Just Salad. Instead, I will terminate any future transactions with Just Salad without hesitation due to my horrible experience. For those customers who also feel VALUELESS at Just Salad I encourage you to suspend further relationships with Just Salad until they hire proper staff (RUDE MANAGER) who at least have a basic understanding of customer service . I hope the manager and those in superior positions take this review seriously and I hope the worker who was going to attempt to take my order find a better job where he is treated with respect from his superiors.
